sublevels.theory:
Templates allow writing type-independent (generic) code.

**Function template:**
```cpp
template<typename T>
T add(T a, T b) { return a + b; }

add(5, 10);    // T=int
add(3.5, 2.2); // T=double
```

**Class template:**
```cpp
template<typename T>
class Box {
    T value;
public:
    Box(T v) : value(v) {}
    T get() const { return value; }
};
Box<int> iBox(42);
Box<std::string> sBox("hi");
```

The compiler generates a separate instantiation for each type used.
